'''Cho Gue-sung''' ({{Korean|hangul=조규성}}; born 25 January 1998) is a South Korean professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as [[Forward (association football)|striker]] for [[Danish Superliga]] club [[FC Midtjylland|Midtjylland]] and the [[South Korea national football team|South Korea national team]].

==Club career==
=== Early career in South Korea ===
Cho played [[Midfielder#Defensive midfielder|defensive midfielder]] during his youth career and freshman year at [[Gwangju University]]. However, Cho was not evaluated as a good midfielder by his university's head coach Lee Seung-won and changed his position to striker in 2017.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.sports-g.com/2019/08/19/%EA%B9%80%ED%98%84%ED%9A%8C-%EA%B2%BD%EC%9F%81%EC%9E%90%EC%9D%B4%EC%9E%90-%EB%8F%99%EB%B0%98%EC%9E%90-%EC%A1%B0%EA%B7%9C%EC%84%B1%EA%B3%BC-%EB%AA%A8%EC%9E%AC%ED%98%84%EC%9D%98 |script-title=ko:경쟁자이자 동반자’ 조규성과 모재현의 특별한 인연 |publisher=Sports-G |language=ko |date=23 June 2019 |access-date=21 August 2019}}</ref>

In 2019, Cho joined [[K League 2]] side [[FC Anyang]] where he was a youth player before.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://sports.news.naver.com/news.nhn?oid=382&aid=0000699912 |script-title=ko:FC안양, 우선지명 포함 2019 신인 5명 영입 |publisher=Sports Donga |date=4 January 2019|language=ko|title=|access-date=2026-05-10|trans-title=FC Anyang signs 5 rookies for 2019, including priority picks}}</ref> He was selected for the K League 2 Best XI after becoming the third highest scorer in his first professional season and transferred to [[K League 1]] club [[Jeonbuk Hyundai Motors]] the next year.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.goal.com/kr/%EB%89%B4%EC%8A%A4/%EC%A1%B0%EA%B7%9C%EC%84%B1%EA%B9%8C%EC%A7%80-%EC%98%81%EC%9E%85%ED%95%9C-%EC%A0%84%EB%B6%81-22%EC%84%B8-%EC%9D%B4%ED%95%98-%EA%B3%A0%EB%AF%BC-%EB%82%A0%EB%A0%B8%EB%8B%A4/61md4a9peaje1i1v39wbjck1o |script-title=ko:조규성까지 영입한 전북, 22세 이하 고민 날렸다 |website=Goal.com |language=ko |date=29 January 2020 |access-date=3 November 2022|title=|trans-title=Jeonbuk, who even signed Cho Gue-sung, blew away their concerns about the under-22 rule}}</ref>

Cho had difficulty proving his worth in his first season at Jeonbuk Hyundai Motors. In 2021, he joined the military team [[Gimcheon Sangmu FC|Gimcheon Sangmu]] to serve his mandatory duty and to get a stable spot.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.chosun.com/sports/sports_photo/2020/12/15/CG42DY7EKWSWI37ZPIFIDZ2FXY/ |script-title=ko:[단독]'이동국 후계자'조규성,상무 입대 결심.."지금이 적기" |publisher=[[The Chosun Ilbo]] |language=ko |date=15 December 2020 |access-date=3 November 2022}}</ref> As a result, he developed physically and technically while being trained at Gimcheon.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.chosun.com/sports/sports_photo/2022/03/06/XI3LHZSOGNGOHMBTGYLC67U2J4/ |script-title=ko:'성장캐' 김천 조규성, 여유에 승리 욕심까지 활활 "뜻대로 안 될 때 스스로 화가 난다" |publisher=[[The Chosun Ilbo]] |language=ko |date=6 March 2022 |access-date=3 November 2022}}</ref> He became the top goalscorer in the [[2022 K League 1]] and led Jeonbuk to the [[2022 Korean FA Cup]] title.

In January 2023, Jeonbuk received transfer bids for him from [[1. FSV Mainz 05|Mainz 05]], [[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]], [[Rangers F.C.|Rangers]] and [[Minnesota United FC|Minnesota United]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Fulton |first=Matthew |date=2023-01-08 |title=Cho Gue-sung Celtic transfer hype intensifies after 'bidding war' |url=https://www.glasgowlive.co.uk/sport/football/cho-gue-sung-celtic-transfer-25924057 |access-date=2023-01-08 |website=GlasgowLive |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Gue-Sung Cho: Celtic in talks over deal {{!}} Rangers monitoring South Korea striker |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/36621/12783608/gue-sung-cho-celtic-in-talks-over-deal-rangers-monitoring-south-korea-striker |access-date=2023-01-11 |website=Sky Sports |language=en|date=2023-01-10|last=Anthony|first=Joseph|last2=Sahil|first2=Jaidka}}</ref> Cho was attracted to Mainz and Celtic but rejected their offers after determining that his physical condition was not good enough to play in Europe.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.xportsnews.com/article/1676798 |script-title=ko:"몸상태 100% 아니다보니"…조규성, 여름 이적으로 기우는 이유 |publisher=Xportsnews |language=ko |date=2023-01-14 |access-date=2023-07-15|title=|trans-title="Not at 100% physical condition"... Why Cho Gue-sung is leaning toward a summer transfer}}</ref>

=== Midtjylland ===

On 11 July 2023, Cho signed with [[Danish Superliga]] club [[FC Midtjylland|Midtjylland]] on a five-year contract for a fee reported to be around £2.6 million.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-07-11 |title=Officielt: FC Midtjylland henter sydkoreansk angriber |url=https://bold.dk/fodbold/klubber/fc-midtjylland/nyheder/officielt-fc-midtjylland-henter-sydkoreansk-angriber |access-date=2026-05-10 |website=Bold |language=da}}</ref> On 22 July 2023, he made his Danish Superliga debut with Midtjylland, scoring in a 1–0 win over [[Hvidovre IF|Hvidovre]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-07-23 |title=조규성, 덴마크 수페르리가 개막전서 데뷔골…미트윌란, 1-0 승리 |url=https://sports.donga.com/sports/article/all/20230723/120367703/1 |access-date=2026-05-10 |website=[[The Dong-A Ilbo]] |language=ko}}</ref> Having a considerable presence at Midtjylland early on, he was selected for the Superliga Team of the Month in July and September.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-08-05 |title=Månedens Hold i juli |trans-title=Team of the Month in July |url=https://x.com/Superligaen/status/1687720865029320704 |access-date=2026-05-10 |website=Twitter.com |publisher=Superliga |language=da}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-09-26 |title=Silkeborg dominans på Månedens Hold i september, hvor hele fire profiler har fundet vej til start 11'eren |url=https://x.com/Superligaen/status/1706672471301054637 |access-date=2026-05-10 |website=Twitter.com |publisher=Superliga |language=da}}</ref>

He won the most duels and aerial duels in the [[2023–24 Danish Superliga]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fotmob.com/en-GB/players/1026781/gue-sung-cho |archive-url=https://archive.today/20240527051704/https://www.fotmob.com/en-GB/players/1026781/gue-sung-cho |title=Gue-Sung Cho |publisher=FotMob |access-date=2024-05-27 |archive-date=2024-05-27}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Silvan |first=Widmer |date=2023-07-11 |title=say88 |url=https://say88s.io |access-date=2026-05-10 |language=da}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.flashscore.dk/nyheder/fodbold-superliga-arets-superligahold-hos-flashscore-blot-en-fcm-spiller-pa-top-fire-domineret-mandskab/WWJOSBMH/ |title=Årets Superligahold hos Flashscore: Blot én FCM-spiller på top fire-domineret mandskab |language=da |publisher=Flashscore |date=2024-05-26 |access-date=2024-05-27|trans-title=Superliga Team of the Year at Flashscore: Only one FCM player on top-four dominated squad}}</ref> He successfully performed the role of target man, while helping his team win the league title.<ref name="champion">{{cite news |url=https://www.fcm.dk/nyheder/reaktioner-paa-mesterskabet-en-vanvittig-foelelse/ |title=Reaktioner på mesterskabet: En vanvittig følelse |language=da |publisher=FC Midtjylland |date=2024-05-26 |access-date=2024-05-27|trans-title=Reactions to the championship: An insane feeling}}</ref>

Cho suffered knee pain during the [[2023–24 FC Midtjylland season|2023–24 season]] and underwent knee surgery at the end of the season to remove his meniscus in Italy. Despite anticipating a full recovery by the start of the [[2024–25 FC Midtjylland season|2024–25 season]], he contracted a bacterial infection which further complicated his rehabilitation and forced him to undergo another operation. This resulted in Cho sitting out the entire 2024–25 season.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Cho Gue-sung back in action after year-long absence |url=https://www.donga.com/en/article/all/20250819/5793856/1 |date=2025-08-19 |access-date=2025-08-21 |work=The Dong-A Ilbo |language=en}}</ref>

On 17 August 2025, Cho made his first appearance in 448 days towards the end of a Superliga match against [[Vejle Boldklub|Vejle]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=448 days since his last match. Today Cho made his return |url=https://www.instagram.com/reel/DNdYuFMtdnD/ |website=Instagram |publisher=FC Midtjylland |date=2025-08-17 |access-date=2025-08-21}}</ref> On 29 September, he scored a bicycle kick goal against [[Randers FC|Randers]], which was selected as the Superliga Goal of the Month.<ref name="gotm">{{cite news |url=https://superliga.dk/nyheder/manedens-mal/25-26/gue-sung-cho-scorede-manedens-mal-i-september |title=Gue-Sung Cho scorede Månedens Mål i september |language=da |publisher=Danish Superliga |date=2025-10-07 |access-date=2025-10-09|trans-title=Gue-Sung Cho scored the Goal of the Month in September}}</ref>

==International career==
Cho made his senior debut for [[South Korea national football team|South Korea]] on 7 September 2021 in a [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification – AFC third round|World Cup qualifier]] against [[Lebanon national football team|Lebanon]].<ref>{{cite web |publisher=FIFA |url=https://www.fifa.com/tournaments/mens/worldcup/qatar2022/qualifiers/afc/match-center/400181508 |title=South Korea v Lebanon game report |date=7 September 2021|access-date=2026-05-10}}</ref> He scored his first international goal on 15 January 2022 in a [[Exhibition game|friendly]] against [[Iceland national football team|Iceland]] at the [[Mardan Sports Complex]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=S. Korea cruise past Iceland 5-1 in men's football friendly |url=https://en.yna.co.kr/view/AEN20220115002100315|publisher=Yonhap News Agency |date=2022-01-15 |access-date=2026-06-03}}</ref>

In November 2022, Cho was named to the 26-man squad for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thenationalnews.com/fifa-world-cup-2022/2022/11/16/south-korea-world-cup-squad-2022/|date=16 November 2022|title=South Korea World Cup squad 2022: Son Heung-min included but 'final decision' to be made}}</ref> In Korea's second match at the tournament, he scored two goals against [[Ghana]] in an eventual 2–3 defeat, becoming the first South Korean player to ever score 2 or more goals in a single World Cup match. Despite losing that match, the goals proved decisive in ultimately sending Korea through to the [[2022 FIFA World Cup knockout stage|Round of 16]] on goal difference, at the expense of [[Uruguay]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=WATCH: Two goals in three minutes! Cho stuns Ghana with quick-fire brace for South Korea {{!}} Goal.com |url=https://www.goal.com/en-us/news/watch-two-goals-three-minutes-cho-stuns-ghana-brace-south-korea/blt84f5e52d75b594f6 |access-date=28 November 2022 |website=goal.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | title=Who is Cho Gue-Sung, the South Korea striker who scored twice vs Ghana in the FIFA World Cup | website=Sportstar | date=28 November 2022 | url=https://sportstar.thehindu.com/football/fifa-world-cup/news/who-is-cho-gue-sung-south-korea-goal-scorer-fifa-world-cup-vs-ghana-qatar-2022/article66196373.ece | access-date=28 November 2022}}</ref> Due to his performance in 2022 FIFA World Cup, Cho proved to be one of the greatest players in the air in Qatar. The young Korean forward won 21 aerial duels, putting him second in terms of success in the air among all players at the World Cup, after Morocco's [[Youssef En-Nesyri]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-01-17 |title=Cho Gue-sung may not be going anywhere this winter: Jeonbuk |url=https://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/2023/01/17/sports/football/Cho-Guesung-Jeonbuk-Hyundai-Motors-Celtic/20230117163003023.html |access-date=2023-01-30 |website=[[Korea JoongAng Daily]] |language=en}}</ref>

Cho was called up for the [[2023 AFC Asian Cup]], and was expected to play as an influential striker for the South Korean national team during [[Hwang Ui-jo]]'s absence.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.fifa.com/fifaplus/en/tournaments/mens/worldcup/canadamexicousa2026/articles/five-stars-world-cup-qualifying-watch-asian-cup |title=Five stars from World Cup qualifying to watch in the Asian Cup |publisher=FIFA |date=2023-12-12 |access-date=2024-02-07}}</ref> However, he disappointed Koreans by missing five big chances and winning only 35% of duels while scoring one goal in six matches (although he did score against Saudi Arabia as the Koreans would win on penalties);<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.sofascore.com/player/gue-sung-cho/1014281 |title=Gue-sung Cho |archive-url=https://archive.today/20240206194015/https://www.sofascore.com/player/gue-sung-cho/1014281 |publisher=Sofascore |archive-date=2024-02-06 |access-date=2024-02-06 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://sports.news.naver.com/news?oid=477&aid=0000472542 |script-title=ko:[카타르 현장] '최악 부진' 조규성 "아쉬움만 남는 대회, 많은 걸 느꼈다" |website=[[Naver]] |publisher=SPOTV News |date=2024-02-07 |access-date=2024-02-07 |language=ko}}</ref> especially after receiving a yellow card for [[Diving (association football)|diving]] instead of shooting in front of [[Jordan national football team|Jordan]]'s goal when Jordan held a 2–0 lead in the 88th minute during the semi-finals.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://sports.news.nate.com/view/20240207n01563 |script-title=ko:'걸리지도 않았는데 넘어진' 조규성, 슈팅 못하고 헐리웃 옐로 [스한 스틸컷] |language=ko |website=[[Nate (web portal)|Nate]] |publisher=Sports Hankook |date=2024-02-07 |access-date=2024-02-07}}</ref>

